The global per diem nurse staffing market is expected to witness significant growth in the coming years, driven by factors such as the increasing demand for healthcare services, the shortage of permanent nursing staff, and the need for flexible staffing solutions in the healthcare industry. The market segmentation based on service type, including emergency department and home care services, reflects the diverse needs of healthcare facilities for temporary nursing staff. The emergency department segment caters to the staffing requirements of acute care settings, ensuring prompt and efficient patient care during critical situations. On the other hand, the home care services segment provides temporary nursing staff for in-home care, catering to the growing demand for personalized and convenient healthcare services.

The end-user segment of the per diem nurse staffing market encompasses hospitals, clinics, nursing homes, and other healthcare facilities, each with unique staffing needs and operational challenges. Hospitals rely on per diem nursing staff to support various departments, including the emergency department, critical care units, and surgical suites. Clinics and outpatient care facilities utilize temporary nursing staff to manage fluctuating patient volumes and ensure smooth operations. Nursing homes and long-term care facilities benefit from per diem nurses who provide ongoing care to residents and promote quality of life through personalized assistance.

